children.subject: I am also a transfer student. I would say it is a good schedule. The first part (out of three) sections of 16A will be the easiest for you because you already took linear algebra. If you struggle, just focus on 61B and don't worry about your grade in 16A. It is very difficult to fail 16A if you put in minimal effort.

history.content:
Hi,

I'm a new transfer student, I took CS61A in the summer(barely made it to the minimum B+ requirement) and I'm currently taking EECS 16A, CS61B, and a GE class, I went to the first class yesterday and EECS16A felt like a very advanced technical course. I was wondering is taking 16A and 61B at the same time the right choice, does it get too much work. I'm very concerned about getting a good grade in 61B to declare the major.
history.subject: Taking EECS 16A and CS61B together
